author_ssm: Naomi Schiller in 2002.  Additional arrangement by Alison Lotto in 2012.
unittitle_ssm: Records of the New York Women's Anthropology Caucus
abstract_ssm: The Records of the New York Women's Anthropology Caucus document the founding and activities of a group of female anthropologists and anthropology students who were active in the New York City and international feminist movements. They were focused on women's rights and were an official non-governmental organization in the United Nations and were active from the 1970s to the 2000s. The records include meeting minutes, newsletters, correspondences, membership lists, funding proposals, scholarly papers, photographs, cassette tapes, and compact discs. Materials date from 1972 to 2002.
